                    "external_url": "",
                    "href": "/docs/api/ops/nonzero",
                    "kind": "link",
                    "target": "nonzero",
                    "text": "nonzero"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " directly should be\npreferred, as it behaves correctly for subclasses. The rest of this\ndocumentation covers only the case where all three arguments are\nprovided."
                  }
                ],
                "type": "paragraph"
              }
            ],
            "directive": "note",
            "options": [],
            "raw_source": ".. note::\n    When only `condition` is provided, this function is a shorthand for\n    ``fnp.asarray(condition).nonzero()``. Using `nonzero` directly should be\n    preferred, as it behaves correctly for subclasses. The rest of this\n    documentation covers only the case where all three arguments are\n    provided.",
